snippet.textDisplay:
Salman I respect your passion and Junoon. But realize this and it's a big statement... Most of the Pink Floyd covers always miss the mark miles away... I can't imagine Chris Martin of Cold Play replacing Eddie Veddar Of Pearl Jam. 

We've waited years for this supposedly epic revival of Junoon on Coke Studio and it's just dampened the spirits. Nothing personal against anyone all are best to Maestro and yourself included. 

Just think of this way Bilal Masood in a right mind would never replace Ali Azmat's power house vocals. No one from Rahat to Ali Noor had method to madness that was Ali Azmat's signature.
